headlines.description: — Moritz Wagner scored 27 points and the Orlando Magic beat the Boston Celtics 113-96 on Friday for their sixth straight win, throwing the Eastern Conference's Group C up for grabs in the NBA's inaugural In-Season Tournament.
headlines.shortLinkText: Moritz Wagner scores 27 to lead Magic over Celtics 113-96 for 6th straight win

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored a season-high 40 points, Eric Gordon added 20 and the Phoenix Suns defeated the Memphis Grizzlies 110-89 in an NBA In-Season Tournament game on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker's 40 points leads Suns past Grizzlies 110-89

events.name: Miami Heat at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson scored 24 points, Immanuel Quickley came off the bench to add 20 and spark a huge turnaround, and the New York Knicks rallied from a 21-point deficit to beat the Miami Heat 100-98 on Friday night and stay alive in the NBA’s In-Season...
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks come from 21 down to beat Heat 100-98 and stay alive in the In-Season Tournament

headlines.description: — O.G. Anunoby matched his season high with 26 points, Pascal Siakam had 18 and the Toronto Raptors beat Chicago 121-108 on Friday night in the NBA’s In-Season Tournament, eliminating the Bulls from contention.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anunoby scores 26 points, Raptors eliminate Bulls from tourney with 121-108 win

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton had 26 points and 10 assists, Myles Turner scored 10 of his 23 points in the final quarter, and the Indiana Pacers earned a quarterfinal home game in the NBA In-Season Tournament with a 136-113 home victory over the Detroit Pistons...
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton, Turner lead Pacers to 136-113 tournament win over Pistons

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 25 points, Alperen Sengun added 21 points and 14 rebounds and the Houston Rockets beat the slumping Denver Nuggets 105-86 on Friday night in the NBA's In-Season Tournament.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green, Sengun lead Rockets to 105-86 victory over Nuggets in NBA's In-Season Tournament

headlines.description: — Brook Lopez matched a career high with 39 points and hit a 3-pointer with 2:40 left to put the Milwaukee Bucks ahead for good in a 131-128 In-Season Tournament victory over the Washington Wizards on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brook Lopez matches career high with 39 points as Bucks edge Wizards 131-128

headlines.description: — De'Aaron Fox had 36 points and 12 assists, and the Sacramento Kings prevented the Minnesota Timberwolves from clinching a spot in the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings stay unbeaten in NBA In-Season Tournament by topping Wolves 124-111 behind Fox's 36 points

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Gary Payton II delivered a defensive gem with his high-leaping block against 7-foot-3 Victor Wembanyama as the Golden State guard returned from a foot injury.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 35 points with seven 3-pointers as Warriors hold off Spurs 118-112

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson scored a season-high 32 points, Brandon Ingram added 30 and the New Orleans Pelicans finished group play in the NBA In-Season Tournament on a winning note, defeating the Los Angeles Clippers 116-106 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williamson scores season-high 32, Pelicans defeat Clippers 116-106 in the In-Season Tournament
